events.name: Golden State Warriors at Orlando Magic

headlines.description: — Stephen Curry scored a season-high 56 points, making 12 3-pointers and outscoring Orlando by himself in the third quarter of another astounding performance, leading the Golden State Warriors to a 121-115 victory over the Magic on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Stephen Curry scores 56 points and makes 12 3-pointers in Warriors' 121-115 win over Magic

headlines.description: — Giannis Antetokounmpo scored 28 points, pulled down a season-high 19 rebounds and dished out seven assists as the Milwaukee Bucks beat the Denver Nuggets 121-112 on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Antetokounmpo has 28 points as Bucks overcome Jokic's triple-double to beat Nuggets 121-112

headlines.description: — Kyrie Irving scored 18 of his 25 points in the second half and grabbed nine rebounds to lead the Dallas Mavericks to a 103-96 victory over the Charlotte Hornets on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Kyrie Irving scores 25, Moses Brown adds 20 points and 11 rebounds in Mavs' 103-96 win over Hornets

events.name: New Orleans Pelicans at Phoenix Suns

headlines.description: — Zion Williamson had his first career triple-double with 27 points, 10 rebounds and 11 assists and the New Orleans Pelicans beat the Phoenix Suns 124-116 on Thursday night for their third straight victory.
headlines.shortLinkText: Zion Williamson has 1st career triple-double, leads the Pelicans to a 124-116 victory over the Suns

events.name: Minnesota Timberwolves at Los Angeles Lakers

headlines.description: — LeBron James had 33 points and 17 rebounds and the Los Angeles Lakers won their fourth straight game, holding off the Minnesota Timberwolves 111-102 on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: LeBron James powers the Lakers to 4th straight victory, 111-102 over the Timberwolves
